view applications of time-domain Brillouin scattering\nfor imaging of nanoporous films, ion-implanted semiconductors and dielectrics,\ntexture in polycrystalline materials and inside vegetable and animal cells, and\nfor monitoring the transformation of nanosound caused by nonlinearity and\nfocusing. We also discuss the perspectives and the challenges for the future.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 9 Jun 2018 10:30:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-12"}
